The Appendix consists of original documents connected with the priory, printed without arrangement, in the order in which we had access to their depositories.

The first seven numbers are taken from the Muniment Room of the Corporation of Dublin, to which we were admitted by an Act of Assembly‚ and where every facility of search was afforded by the kindness and attention of Mr. William Ford, Town Clerk.

No, XIII„ the Visitation of this Priory in 1468, is taken from Archbishop Tregury's Register, preserved in Trinity College.

The remaining numbers are printed from the original volume of Archbishop Alan’s Registry, in the possession of the Archbishop of Dublin, which His Grace put into the hands of Dr. Todd sor the pur- poses of this work⁸.
